******
[1] Iran, backyard poultry
Date: 18 Jan 2007
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health
Information Database) Disease Information 2008; 21(3) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Highly pathogenic avian influenza, Iran
-------------------------------------------
Information received on 16 Jan 2008 from Dr. Mojtaba Noorouzi
Head of Iran Veterinary Organization
Iran Veterinary Organization State
Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture
Iran Veterinary Organization (IVO), TEHERAN, Iran

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 10 Dec 2007
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 12 Dec 2007
Report date: 16 Jan 2008
Date submitted to OIE: 16 Jan 2008
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence; February 2006
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Highly pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory
(basic), Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Darzi Naghib, Babolsar, MAZANDARAN
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Dec 2007
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village

Species: birds
Susceptible: 489
Cases: 14
Deaths: 14
Destroyed: 475
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: free-range chickens (backyard)

Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species: birds
Apparent morbidity rate: 2.86%
Apparent mortality rate: 2.86%
Apparent case fatality rate: 100.00%
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 100.00%
* Removed from the susceptible population through
death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin
of infection. Under investigation.

Epidemiological comments: The event was reported
according to the Iranian passive surveillance
programme in place; a post-outbreak investigation
to trace the source of the infection is ongoing
to detect the probable spread and circulation of
the virus. Active surveillance is ongoing.

Laboratory name and type: Iran Veterinary
Organization (IVO) Central Laboratory (National laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: real-time PCR
Test date: 12 Dec 2007
Result: positive

Laboratory name and type Istituto Zooprofilattico
Sperimentale delle Venezie (IZSV), Padova (Italy) (OIE’s Reference Laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: real time gene sequencing
Test date: 8 Jan 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: reverse transcription ­ polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date: 8 Jan 2008
Result: positive

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2] India, backyard poultry
Date: 18 Jan 2007
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health
Information Database) Disease Information 2008; 21(3) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Highly pathogenic avian influenza, India
------------------------------------------
Information received on 15/01/2008 from Dr/ Pradeep Kumar
Secretary to the Government of India
Department of Animal Husbandry, Dairying and Fisheries
Ministry of Agriculture, New Delhi, India

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 4 Jan 2008
Date of first confirmation of the event: 15 Jan 2008
Report date: 15 Jan 2008
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Jan 2008
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2 Aug 2007
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Highly pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Rampurhat, Nalhati, Mayureswar, Rampurhat, Birbhum, WEST BENGAL
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Jan 2008
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village

Species: birds
Susceptible: 819 078
Cases: 35 525
Deaths: 35 525
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: backyard poultry mainly in
small and marginal farms in 3 villages.
Note by the OIE's Animal Health Information
Department: This information is a sum up of outbreaks occurring in 3 villages.
Outbreak 2: Balurghat, Balurghat, Dakshin Dinajpur, WEST BENGAL
Date of start of the outbreak: 7 Jan 2008
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm

Species: birds
Susceptible: 1710
Cases: 261
Deaths: 261
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: a small farm with a capacity for about 2000 birds

Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 2

Species: birds
Susceptible: 820 788
Cases: 35 786
Deaths: 35 786
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak statistics
Species: birds
Apparent morbidity rate: 4.36 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 4.36 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100.00 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 4.36 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through
death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin
of infection. Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Epidemiological
investigation is ongoing. Stamping out of all
domestic poultry is being applied in an
approximately 5-km-radius [3.1-mile] zone around
the outbreaks followed by compensation of the
owners. An intensive surveillance campaign has
been launched in a 10-km-radius [6.2-mile] zone including:
-- closure of poultry markets and prohibition on
sale and transportation of poultry products in the infected zone;
-- disinfection of premises after culling and
sealing of premises where appropriate.
Restocking will be applied in accordance with a specific protocol.

Laboratory name and type: High Security Animal
Disease Laboratory, Bhopal (National laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: haemagglutination (HA) test
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: Birds haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT)
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: real-time PCR
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: reverse transcription ­ polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: virus isolation
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

National Institute of Virology, Pune (National laboratory)

Species: birds
Test: real-time PCR
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: reverse transcription ­ polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date: 15 Jan 2008
Result: positive

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The location of the outbreak in Iran is located
near the Caspian Sea, which can be seen at
<http://www.travelpost.com/ME/Iran/Gilan/Mazandaran_Mahalleh/map/6879109>.
The outbreak locations in India is very close to
the border with Bangladesh, see map at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birbhum_District> and
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Dinajpur>. - Mod.PC]
